description:
We dare you to find better value!

The hardest part has been done with 95% of the house having had its interior torn out and replaced with modern fixtures, fittings, built in appliances, colour palate and even floor plan. All that’s left is the bathrooms for the new owner to make their own personal touch. We’ve even made allowance for this in the price!

Outside has had stables erected and irrigation taps throughout the house yard have been established to pump water from the larger of the two dams to keep the parklike and picturesque driveway looking perfect all year around.

And the location!!! This property is set between some of the best features this region has to offer. If you like anything between forest trails or the beaches, this property is close to all your outdoor fun. Once the highway bypass of Gympie is complete, this property will be only 5 minutes from being on the highway headed up or down the coast.

Location:

This property is 14 minutes East of Gympie CBD and is a tightly held location situated near beautiful beaches and National parks. 60 minutes to Noosa, 45 minutes Rainbow beach and 2 hours North from Brisbane. Gympie is situated between Noosa and Fraser Island, and is part of South East Queensland, one of the fastest growing regions in Australia. The Cooloola Region centres on the historic city of Gympie and includes the Cooloola Coast and the Mary Valley.

House:

Modernised brick home with sheds, stables, paddocks, views and so much more close to everything and anything you could want to do. Pure lifestyle luxury is on offer with this rare 27.77 acre property!

Features:

Rejuvenated interior with modern and stylish fitting and fixtures.

Open plan living with air conditioning and ceiling fan.

Kitchen with massive walk in pantry, built in microwave, built in electric oven, built in coffee station, touch sensor electric cooktop with heat dispersion vent, stone benchtops, light up display cabinet, light up display wine rack & press to open drawers.

2 x XL bedrooms with plush carpet, air conditioning, built in wardrobes with a bathroom situated between them.

XXL Master suite with plush carpets, walk in wardrobe, ensuite, air conditioning & TV wall mount bracket.

Large internal laundry with indoor/outdoor access.

Enclosed sunroom with indoor/outdoor access and views of stables.

Outside:

Stables facility with 5 stable bays, powered tac room, two water storage tanks & 2 yards.

Sand arena in bottom paddock.

Fully fenced with multiple paddocks.

Parklike grounds with picturesque views with a scenic driveway entry.

Outdoor entertaining area with lush garden views, brick BBQ & wood fire pizza oven.

Dual bay, sandstone block, powered shed with personnel door and additional 2 bay carport attached.

Single bay colorbond shed with personnel door an additional 2 bay carport attached.

2 x large dams.

Seasonal creek.

Garden irrigation taps connected to concrete water tank, pumped up from the lower dam.

55,000 litre water storage under outdoor entertaining area connected with dual media and UV filtration system.

27.77 acres/11.11 hectares of rolling hill and paddocks.

Lightly timbered with mixed hardwood trees.

Good land that will grow a variety of produce, plants and feed for all the animals.

Zoned- Rural Residential.

Contact the team at agents2go to arrange your personal inspection. You will love it!
